{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLib","role":"symbol","externalID":"s:4GLib19MainContextProtocolPAAE17pushThreadDefaultyyF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib11MainContextC","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"pushThreadDefault","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"title":"pushThreadDefault()"},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext\/pushThreadDefault()","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext\/pushthreaddefault()"]}],"abstract":[{"text":"Acquires ","type":"text"},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"(such as most "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html"},{"type":"text","text":"-based I\/O) which are"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"started in this thread to run under "},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"changes the context returned by [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not the one returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.default"},{"text":"], so it does not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"affect the context used by functions like [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pushThreadDefault"},{"kind":"text","text":"()"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Normally you would call this function shortly after creating a new","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thread, passing it a [struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"text":"] which will be run by a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] in that thread, to set a new default context for all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"async operations in that thread. In this case you may not need to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ever call [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"], assuming you want"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the new [struct"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"] to be the default for the whole lifecycle"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"of the thread.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If you don’t have control over how the new thread was created (e.g.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the new thread isn’t newly created, or if the thread life"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"cycle is managed by a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool"},{"text":"), it is always suggested to wrap","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the logic that needs to use the new [struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] inside a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"text":"] pair, otherwise threads that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"are re-used will end up never explicitly releasing the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true},{"text":"] reference they hold.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In some cases you may want to schedule a single operation in a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"non-default context, or temporarily use a non-default context in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the main thread. In that case, you can wrap the call to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"asynchronous operation inside a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] \/","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.pop_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"] pair, but it is up to you to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"ensure that no other asynchronous operations accidentally get"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"started while the non-default context is active.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Beware that libraries that predate this function may not correctly","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"handle being used from a thread with a thread-default context. For example,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"see "},{"code":"g_file_supports_thread_contexts()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext\/MainContextProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"kind":"symbol","role":"collection","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","title":"GLib","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext/MainContextProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"MainContextProtocol Implementations","type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext\/MainContextProtocol-Implementations","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext\/maincontextprotocol-implementations"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPool":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct represents a thread pool.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"ThreadPool","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool"},"../gio/index.html":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Gio"}],"type":"link","url":"..\/gio\/index.html","identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","title":"Gio"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMainContext"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainContext"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","title":"MainContext"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainLoop":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainLoop","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GMainLoop"},{"type":"text","text":" struct is an opaque data type"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"representing the main event loop of a GLib or GTK application."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/mainloop","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MainLoop"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainLoop","title":"MainLoop"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext/pushThreadDefault()":{"abstract":[{"text":"Acquires ","type":"text"},{"code":"context","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and sets it as the thread-default context for the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"current thread. This will cause certain asynchronous operations","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(such as most "},{"identifier":"..\/gio\/index.html","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"-based I\/O) which are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"started in this thread to run under "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"context"},{"type":"text","text":" and deliver their"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"results to its main loop, rather than running under the global"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"default main context in the main thread. Note that calling this function","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"changes the context returned by [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.get_thread_default"},{"type":"text","text":"],"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"not the one returned by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.MainContext.default"},{"type":"text","text":"], so it does not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"affect the context used by functions like [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.idle_add"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"pushThreadDefault"},{"text":"()","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext\/pushThreadDefault()","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext\/pushthreaddefault()","title":"pushThreadDefault()"}}}